                <h1>Understanding the Importance of the Spine</h1>
                <p>The spine, an essential component of the vertebrate skeleton, provides structural support and protects the spinal cord. Composed of 33 vertebrae, it enables flexibility, movement, and balance. The spine also plays a crucial role in posture and overall health, influencing how we move and interact with our environment.</p>
